# Java conventions

## Import order

1. `java.*` / `javax.*` / `jakarta.*`
2. `io.quarkus.*`
3. Third-party
4. `dev.vepo.issues.*`

## Style

- Formatting: [issues-format-imports.mdc](issues-format-imports.mdc) — `formatter.xml`, no unused imports.
- String building: [issues-strings.mdc](issues-strings.mdc) — `.formatted()` first; no `+` concatenation in production code.
- **Type names:** PascalCase classes, records, enums.

## `var`

- Prefer `var` when the RHS type is clear. Keep explicit types on fields and public API signatures.

## Logging

- SLF4J only — never `System.out`.
- One static logger per class: `LoggerFactory.getLogger(MyClass.class)`.
- Parameterized messages; pass exception as last arg on `error`.
- Do not log passwords or JWT tokens.

## Entities

- `jakarta.persistence`; table prefix `tb_`; `Long` ids.
- Lazy associations by default; fetch in queries when needed for responses.

## Exceptions

- Domain errors: `IssuesException` in `infra`.
- Map to HTTP via `IssuesWebExceptionMapper` / `IssuesServerExceptionMapper`.
